Professor seems to have a loose relationship with the truth. Claims that 90% of new products fail, when that's a well-debunked urban legend. Claims that products can't improve in more than 1 way against competitors, even though there's tons of documented cases of that happening. There's just a whole lot of wrong facts here, and not a whole lot of substance here. Plus the main benefit of MBA programs is getting to meet other enterprising people, but the forums here are dead and spammy. Most posts are just people asking for easy As on their homeworks.
